              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Windowless hydrogen gas target filled with H2 at an",
                "average pressure and temperature of 10.6 mbar",
                "and 298 K, respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BGO"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Array of 30 bismuth germanate (BGO) detectors",
                "surrounding the windowless gas target was used to",
                "detect gamma rays resulting from the (p,gamma)",
                "reaction,"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 39Ca recoils were transmitted to the focal",
                "plane of DRAGON spectrometer and were identified using",
                "time-of-flight system and an isobutane-filled",
                "ionization chamber"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MCPLT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Time-of-flight (TOF) system was based on two",
                "microchannel plates detecting secondary electron",
                "emission from thin diamondlike carbon foils."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The total kinetic energy and stopping power",
                "of the recoil ions was measured in a multi-anode",
                "ionization chamber"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Number of incident 19Ne ions was determined by",
                "measuring 19Ne beta decays in two 6-mm-thick plastic",
                "scintillators located near an intermediate focus of",
                "the separator where the 6+ component of the unreacted",
                "beam was stopped."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Coincidences between gamma rays detected in",
                "BGO array and recoil nuclei, detected by ionization",
                "chamber was required.",
                "Inverse kinematics was used"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "SPALL"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " A beam of radioactive 38K was produced by",
                "impinging 500 MeV protons from the TRIUMF cyclotron",
                "onto a high-power TiC production target. The 38K(1+)",
                "produced by spallation reactions in the target",
                "were extracted and sent through a high-resolution",
                "mass separator. They were then charge bred to the 7+",
                "charge state in an electron cyclotron resonance (ECR)",
                "charge state booster before post-acceleration in",
                "ISAC-1 radiofrequency quadrupole."
              ]
            }
          ],
